-- Bank of Africa Opens Two Branches in Paris Amid Expansion, La Tribune Says
-- Tara Patel
-- 2010-07-23T06:02:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/bank-of-africa-opens-two-branches-in-paris-amid-expansion-la-tribune-says.html

          
          
             Bank of Africa NG  opened two
branches in Paris as part of an effort to expand in France,  La
Tribune  reported, citing Chairman Paul Derreumaux.  
 The bank plans to open branches in Belgium, Italy and Spain
to handle money transfers between European and African
countries, the newspaper said.  
